# Testing

Run the **smallest scope that catches your regression** after substantive edits. Full gate: `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify` before marking done — see [static-analysis.mdc](static-analysis.mdc).

**Session end:** never stop with failing tests in your diff ([development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Working code invariant).

## Tiered ladder

| When | Command |
|------|---------|
| Trivial / compile-only edit | Skip until next substantive change |
| One package edited | `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=ClassName` |
| Endpoint + template changed | Related `*WebTest` or `*Test` + navigation if user-facing |
| CSS/JS/template only | Affected `@WebTest` or `scripts/audit-template-seo.sh` when SEO/chrome |
| Task done | `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify` |

```bash
# Full gate (matches CI)
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify

# Single test class
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=PostWebTest

# Single method
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=PostWebTest#shouldShowPost

# Unit profile (faster)
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Ptest-unit

# Web profile
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Ptest-web

# Architecture rules
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Dtest=BoundedContextRulesTest

# Dev mode (manual)
./mvnw quarkus:dev
```

## Impact map

| You changed | Run |
|-------------|-----|
| `post/*` | `Post*Test`, `Post*WebTest` |
| `auth/*`, `user/*` | `Auth*Test`, `User*Test` |
| `readinglist/*` | `ReadingList*Test`, `ReadingList*WebTest` |
| `seo/*`, templates (meta/href) | `SeoServiceTest`, `SeoWebTest`, `scripts/audit-template-seo.sh` |
| `highlight/*` | `Highlight*Test`, `Highlight*WebTest` |
| `shared/architecture/*` | `BoundedContextRulesTest` |
| `components/header.html`, menu | `*WebTest` touching navigation + SEO audit |
| `dev-import.sql` | Restart `quarkus:dev`; smoke-click affected feature |

Detail: [contraponto-tests.mdc](contraponto-tests.mdc), [test-headless-github-actions.mdc](test-headless-github-actions.mdc).

TDD: [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Phase 5; subagents `tdd-red`, `tdd-green`, `tdd-refactor`.

## When tests fail

1. Re-run smallest repro — [contraponto-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc](contraponto-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc).
2. Do not loop full `verify` per fix attempt.
3. After green: optional report under `reports/` per that rule.

## Infra to reuse

- `Given` builders — never raw repository setup in test methods.
- `App` DSL — never raw WebDriver in `@WebTest` methods.
- `Given.cleanup()` when tests mutate shared data.
- No `Thread.sleep()` — use explicit waits in `App` only when unavoidable.
